<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="pity-n">pity <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pɪti/    美 /'pɪti/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 同情；怜悯：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We helped her out of pity.
我们出于怜悯帮助了她。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The owner of the house <strong>took pity on</strong> us and let us come in out of the rain.
房主同情我们，让我们进屋避雨。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c-shame">2.★ <strong>[C] [用单数] 可惜的事；憾事 (shame)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>What a pity</strong>! 
真可惜！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It was a pity</strong> (<strong>that</strong>) you could not come. 
你不能来真是遗憾。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The pity was that the winner couldn’t be there to receive the prize. 
遗憾的是获奖者不能前来领奖。</p><footer>2009 福建改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— Can you come to a party on Saturday, Peter?
— Oh, what pity! I’m already going out, I’m afraid.  （2015 安徽改 改错）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. pity 前加 a  </p></div>